def show_overlayed_images(original_image, label_image, pred_image):
    grayscale_label = label_image
    colored_label = np.zeros_like(original_image)
    colored_label[..., 2] = label_image

    overlay_label = cv2.addWeighted(original_image, 0.5, colored_label, 0.5, 0)
    colored_pred = np.zeros_like(original_image)
    colored_pred[..., 0] = pred_image

    overlay_pred = cv2.addWeighted(original_image, 0.5, colored_pred, 0.5, 0)
    combined_overlay = cv2.addWeighted(overlay_label, 0.7, overlay_pred, 0.7, 0)

    
    plt.figure(figsize=(22, 12))
    
    plt.subplot(141)
    plt.imshow(original_image)
    plt.title('Original Image')

    plt.subplot(142)
    plt.imshow(overlay_label)
    plt.title('Overlayed Label')

    plt.subplot(143)
    plt.imshow(overlay_pred)
    plt.title('Overlayed Prediction')

    plt.subplot(144)
    plt.imshow(combined_overlay)
    plt.title('Combined Overlay')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
In[12]:
class SegmentationDataset(Dataset):
    """Image (semantic) segmentation dataset."""

    def __init__(self, feature_extractor, files):
        self.feature_extractor = feature_extractor
        self.files = files

        self.id2label = {0: "background", 1: "fish"}

    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.files)

    def __getitem__(self, idx):
        image = Image.open(self.files[idx]['image'])
        segmentation_map = Image.open(self.files[idx]['label'])
        segmentation_array = np.array(segmentation_map)

        segmentation_array = np.max(segmentation_array, axis=-1)
        # Convert 255 values to 1
        segmentation_array = segmentation_array // 255

        segmentation_map = Image.fromarray(segmentation_array)
        encoded_inputs = self.feature_extractor(image, segmentation_map, return_tensors="pt")
        for k, v in encoded_inputs.items():
            encoded_inputs[k].squeeze_()

        return encoded_inputs

# File paths for each category
original_base_path = '../../Dataset/salmon_segmentation/out/1.'
label_base_path = '../../Dataset/salmon_segmentation/out/2.'
categories = ['01--', '02--', '03--', '04--']

# Accumulate file names from each category
paired_files = []
for category in categories:
    path_original = os.path.join(original_base_path, category)
    path_label = os.path.join(label_base_path, category)

    original_files = sorted([os.path.join(path_original, f) for f in os.listdir(path_original) if f.endswith(('.jpg', '.png'))])
    label_files = sorted([os.path.join(path_label, f) for f in os.listdir(path_label) if f.endswith('.png')])

    paired_files.extend([{"image": img, "label": lbl} for img, lbl in zip(original_files, label_files)])

random.seed(42)
random.shuffle(paired_files)

num_train = int(0.8 * len(paired_files))
num_val = int(0.1 * len(paired_files))
num_test = len(paired_files) - num_train - num_val

train_files, val_files, test_files = random_split(paired_files, [num_train, num_val, num_test])

train_dataset = SegmentationDataset(feature_extractor, train_files)
val_dataset = SegmentationDataset(feature_extractor, val_files)
test_dataset = SegmentationDataset(feature_extractor, test_files)

batch_size = 8
train_dataloader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=True)
val_dataloader = DataLoader(val_dataset, batch_size=batch_size)
test_dataloader = DataLoader(test_dataset, batch_size=batch_size)

data = []

for idx, batch in enumerate(tqdm(val_dataloader)):
    images, masks = batch['pixel_values'], batch['labels']
    outputs = load_model(images)
    upsampled_outputs = nn.functional.interpolate(
        outputs[0], 
        size=masks.shape[-2:], 
        mode="bilinear", 
        align_corners=False
    )
    predicted = upsampled_outputs.argmax(dim=1)
    results = load_metric('mean_iou').compute(
        predictions=predicted, 
        references=batch['labels'], 
        num_labels=2, 
        ignore_index=255
    )
    
    result_dict = {'image_idx': idx}
    for key, value in results.items():
        result_dict[key] = value
    data.append(result_dict)

result_df = pd.DataFrame(data)
result_df['backgournd_iou'] = result_df['per_category_iou'].apply(lambda x: x[0])
result_df['foreground_iou'] = result_df['per_category_iou'].apply(lambda x: x[1])
result_df['backgournd_acc'] = result_df['per_category_accuracy'].apply(lambda x: x[0])
result_df['foreground_acc'] = result_df['per_category_accuracy'].apply(lambda x: x[1])
result_df = result_df.drop(columns=['per_category_iou', 'per_category_accuracy'])
mean_values = result_df.mean()
result_df = result_df.append(mean_values, ignore_index=True)

result_df
